1)join - The split() method divides a String into an ordered set of substrings, puts these substrings into an array, 
    and returns the array.  The division is done by searching for a pattern; where the pattern is provided as the 
    first parameter in the method's call.
        
        str.split([separator[, limit]])
        "sumeet".split() => ["sumeet"]
        "sumeet".split('i') => ["sumeet"] 
        "sumeet".split("") => ["s","u","m","e","e","t"]